Revision history for Linux-Event

0.001  2026-02-05
    - Initial release
    - High-performance event framework using io_uring
    - Features:
      * I/O watchers (read/write polling)
      * One-shot timers
      * Periodic timers
      * Signal handlers
      * Idle callbacks
      * Deferred execution
      * File/directory watching (inotify via Linux::Inotify2)
      * Filesystem monitoring (fanotify via Linux::Fanotify)
      * Watcher management (start/stop/priority)
      * Priority-based event processing
      * Clean, intuitive API
    - Built on IO::Uring::Easy for simplified io_uring access
    - Complete examples:
      * HTTP server
      * Echo server
      * Timer demonstrations
      * Deferred/idle callback examples
      * File watching with inotify
      * Filesystem monitoring with fanotify
    - Comprehensive documentation and tests
    - Kernel compatibility:
      * Core features: Linux 5.1+ (io_uring)
      * File watching: Linux 2.6.13+ (inotify)
      * Filesystem monitoring: Linux 2.6.37+/5.1+ (fanotify)
